name: HTML
definition: HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the code that is used to structure a web page and its content.

name: CSS
definition: Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML.

name: Bootstrap
definition: Bootstrap is a free, open source front-end development framework for the creation of websites and web apps

name: Tailwind
definition: Tailwind CSS makes it quicker to write and maintain the code of your application.

name: JavaScript
definition: JavaScript is a scripting or programming language that allows you to implement complex features on web pages.

name: React
definition: React is a declarative, efficient, and flexible JavaScript library for building user interfaces.
